WEBVTT

00:00:00.100 --> 00:00:04.525
The truth about learning Energy reserves 1 Our bodies can

00:00:04.537 --> 00:00:07.450
be seen as rechargeable batteries that provide energy to the

00:00:07.475 --> 00:00:13.463
brain Nutrition intake and relaxation are like recharging 2 Everyone

00:00:13.488 --> 00:00:18.525
has different battery energy levels 3 Actively improve energy storage

00:00:18.538 --> 00:00:22.825
capacity engage in moderate and long-term exercise like a 45-minute

00:00:22.837 --> 00:00:26.725
jog every day 4 The habit of long-term jogging is

00:00:26.750 --> 00:00:30.988
less likely to be interrupted if developed early 5 Walking

00:00:31.137 --> 00:00:36.962
jogging and meditation are equivalent 6 Meditation complete relaxation of

00:00:36.987 --> 00:00:41.538
the cerebral cortex with no active mental work 7 Outdoor

00:00:41.562 --> 00:00:45.712
exercise is best done in sunlight 8 During sleep the

00:00:45.725 --> 00:00:48.938
brain repeats and replays events that occurred before falling asleep

00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:54.225
9 Reviewing lessons before bedtime helps consolidate information during sleep

00:00:55.100 --> 00:00:59.712
10 Sleep quality is related to learning quality 11 Avoid

00:00:59.737 --> 00:01:02.300
exposure to blue light half an hour before bedtime

